YBNL former signee, Temmy Ovwasa has said life would have been a lot easier for her if she wasn’t a queer. The singer who has always been vocal about her sexual orientation made this statement during a recent podcast. Temmy said if she had the willpower to be straight, she would choose the baby girl lifestyle. She noted that her sexual orientation deprives her of so many good things.   How I battled health crisis in 2021, by Ngozi Nwosu     Uproar as Mercy Aigbe finally unveils new ‘boo’     Pasuma: I’ve recorded 60 albums in my 37 years on…   - Advertisement - “Life would have been a lot easier if I wasn’t, there are so many things I can’t do because I’m queer,” she said. “It’s not even because anybody is trying to be wicked to me. Ok, my friends are going to hang out with one rich man but I cannot go there because I will just be there to be the third party. “The system is set up in such a way that a lot of women are actively involved in work that requires men to thrive and that is the issue I have. What of those of us that cannot cater to that demographic,” she said.